definition.value: The external part of the developing pharynx that is made of ectoderm. During vertebrate development, pockets form in pharyngeal ectoderm between the pharyngeal arches.

label.value: central nervous system gray matter layer

definition.value: A layer of of the central nervous system that is part of gray matter.

label.value: central nervous system white matter layer

definition.value: A layer of of the central nervous system that is composed of white matter.
Mucus produced in the respiratory tract.
Any mucus produced by a mucosae of the respiratory system. This includes the mucus produced in the nasal cavity (nasal mucus) and mucus produced in the respiratory tract (phlegm).
A white matter that is part of the midbrain.
A blood vessel that is part of a cerebellum.
An roughly circular indentation in a surface.
An acellular membrane in the vestibular labyrinth that is composed of the otoconial layer, gelatinous layer, and a subcupular meshwork.

An acellular membrane in the inner ear that is part of the statoconial membrane and consists of long branching filaments cross-bridged to one another. The filaments are continuous with those of the otolithic membrane on one side and with the surface of the epithelium on the other.

label.value: lamina of gray matter of spinal cord

definition.value: A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 1 that develop into the tragus, crus of the helix, and helix.
A collection of protruberances derived from pharyngeal arch 2 that develop into the concha, antihelix and antitragus.
The dorsal region of the optic cup that gives rise to the dorsal part of the retina.
The ventral region of the optic cup that gives rise to the ventral part of the retina.
Primordium that develops into the central nervous system.
Primordium that develops into the nervous system.

The joint that is formed by the union of the humerus, the scapula (or shoulder blade), and the clavicle (or collarbone). Commonly thought of as a single joint, the shoulder is actually made up of two separate joints - the glenohumeral and acromioclavicular joints.

label.value: epithelium of terminal part of digestive tract

definition.value: Epithelium lining the distalmost portion of the digestive tract.

label.value: muscle tissue of terminal part of digestive tract

definition.value: Any muscle tissue of the distalmost portion of the digestive tract.
The part of the conceptus that may be lost before birth or will be discarded at birth, or when the embryo becomes an independent organism.
An embryonic anatomical entity that will turn into one or more other anatomical entities, perhaps with other anatomical entities, later in development.
A metaphysis that is part of a fibula.
A bony structure embedded in skin, roughly equivalent to osteoderms.
A sesamoid element that is part of a tarsal skeleton.
A set of teeth in which each tooth that attaches to a vomer.
A structure with numerous blood vessels (retia mirabilia) in the gas bladder that secretes gases from the blood.
The ventral part of the body wall.
The dorsal part of the body wall.
A mesenchyme-derived anatomical entity undergoing a transtion to become another structure.
A primordium that has the potential to develop into a saliva-secreting gland.
A viscus that is part of a abdomen.
A mesopodial endochondral element that is in the most proximal part of the mesopodial skeleton, connected to the zeugopodial skeleton.
A proximal mesopodial endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
A muscle layer that is part of the rectum.
Any portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of the rectum.
A kidney interstitium that is part of a left kidney.
A kidney interstitium that is part of a right kidney.
A renal pelvis that is part of a left ureter.
A renal pelvis that is part of a right ureter.
A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a left kidney.
A renal cortex interstitium that is part of a right kidney.
A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a left kidney.
A renal medulla interstitium that is part of a right kidney.
Encapsulated adipose tissue that is part of a tail.
